            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer against the evil eye, usually followed by the legend of the witch seen by the Apostles on the shore of the 
                    <placeName ref="LOC7368Tiberias">Sea of Galilee (Tiberias)</placeName>. The prayer begins with the name of an eye disease (or, alternatively, a demon that causes it), or with several such names. 
                    The most common are <foreign xml:lang="gez">nadarā</foreign> (also <foreign xml:lang="gez">nadǝrā, nǝd(ǝ)rā</foreign>) and  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʿāynat</foreign>. Other demons might be included. 
                    It also contains an ʾasmāt-prayer of various types, which may potentially be given a separate ID.</p>
            </abstract>
